Git Quick Reference

1. Check Status

git status

2. Fetch Latest Changes

git fetch origin

3. Pull Latest Changes

git pull origin

4. Push Changes

git push origin

5. Merge Target Branch

git checkout git merge origin/develop

6. Abort Merge

git merge –abort

7. Keep Your Current Changes (During Merge)

Specific file: git checkout –ours git add

All conflicted files: git checkout –ours . git add . git commit

8. Keep Incoming Changes

Specific file: git checkout –theirs git add

All conflicted files: git checkout –theirs . git add . git commit

9. List Conflicted Files

git diff –name-only –diff-filter=U

10. Cherry-pick a Commit

git cherry-pick

11. Cherry-pick a Merge Commit

git cherry-pick -m 1

12. Continue Cherry-pick

git add . git cherry-pick –continue

13. Abort Cherry-pick

git cherry-pick –abort

14. Rebase

git rebase origin/develop

15. Continue Rebase

git add . git rebase –continue

16. Abort Rebase

git rebase –abort

17. Stash Changes

git stash git stash list git stash pop

18. View Branches

git branch git branch -a

19. View Commit History

git log –oneline –graph –decorate

20. Recover Deleted Commits

git reflog

Notes: - During a merge: –ours = your current branch –theirs = branch
being merged. - During a rebase: ours/theirs are reversed.

 Tip: git fetch origin git checkout git merge origin/develop

Resolve conflicts locally, then push your branch before creating or
updating a PR.
